### Create a Reactive Blank Template Project using Expo CLI
1. Change terminal from push to git bash
2. Run CD desktop to change the directory
3. Run npx create-expo-app --template to create the expo app
4. Choose blank as your template 
5. Give a name to the app. It will automatically install the app 
6.  Run cd "app name"
7. Run npx start . This would automatically generate a QR code and a URL.
8. Install Expo Go app on your phone. Scan the QR code with the expo app. This would generate your blank template


### Change Background Color of the View Component

In the App.js file, locate the <View> component.
Add a style prop to the <View> component and set the backgroundColor property to the desired color (e.g., backgroundColor: 'beige').


### Edit the Text Component

Inside the <View> component, locate the <Text> component.
Replace the existing text with "My name is Yeboah Gertrude Asabea".


### Increase Font Size of the Text

Add a style prop to the <Text> component.
Set the fontSize property to 24 (e.g., style={{ fontSize: 24 }}).


### Make "Yeboah Gertrude Asabea" Bold

Wrap the text "Yeboah Gertrude Asabea" with another <Text> component.
Add a style prop to the nested <Text> component and set the fontWeight property to 'bold' (e.g., style={{ fontWeight: 'bold' }}).

